### CVE-2024-49981 Patch Information

#### Summary of the Vulnerability
- **CVE ID:** CVE-2024-49981
- **Description:** This vulnerability involves a use-after-free bug in the `venus_remove` function due to a race condition. It affects the Linux kernel stable tree.

#### Recommended Patch
- **Patch Type:** Code Fix
- **Commit Reference:** `kernel/git/stable/linux.git`
- **Patch Description:** The patch addresses the use-after-free vulnerability by ensuring proper synchronization in the `venus_remove` function to prevent race conditions.

#### Code Snippet
```c
// Example code snippet illustrating the fix
void venus_remove(struct venus_device *vdev) {
    mutex_lock(&vdev->lock);

    // Ensure that the resource is not freed while in use
    if (vdev->is_active) {
        // Perform necessary cleanup
        cleanup_resources(vdev);
    }

    mutex_unlock(&vdev->lock);
}
```

#### Additional Information
- **Repository:** [Linux Kernel Stable Tree](https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/stable/linux.git)
- **Patch Location:** The specific patch can be found within the commits related to the `venus` subsystem in the stable branch.

