| **Privilege Escalation** | Abuse Elevation Control Mechanism | By manipulating the `led_access` mutex, attackers could escalate privileges, allowing them to execute arbitrary code with elevated permissions. |
| **Defense Evasion**      | Process Injection                | Attackers may use this vulnerability to inject malicious code into processes that have higher privileges, evading detection mechanisms. |
| **Impact**               | Data Manipulation                | Successful exploitation may lead to unauthorized access to system data or manipulation of system settings, impacting system integrity. |

